version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2026-06-15
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/samyama-ai/lsm-bloom-allocation"
keywords:
  - LSM-tree
  - Bloom filter
  - approximate membership
  - workload adaptivity
  - RocksDB
abstract: >
  A pre-registered study of when workload-adaptive LSM Bloom-filter tuning is worth its machinery.
  The optimal bits-per-key is affine in log access-frequency (the log-law), so the optimal allocation
  is robust to hotness-estimation error (excess cost = D/2, common-factor-immune), and the value of
  continuous online tracking over a coarse allocation recomputed only at compaction is governed by a
  two-clock frontier with closed form r* = sqrt(2 (C_uniform - C_oracle)/C_oracle). Validated on
  synthetic sweeps, real Twitter production cache traces, and a real RocksDB engine.
